What is ORM?

ORM (Object Relational Mapping) is a technique that maps C# classes to database tables. It allows developers to work with database data as C# objects instead of writing SQL queries manually.

Benefits
Increases productivity.
Easy to maintain.
Reduces SQL code.
Provides abstraction from the database.


